@DATABASE "PMP"
@WIDTH 77
@NODE "MAIN" "Welcome to Pink Mouse's Planetarium"
@TOC "MAIN"


                 Pink Mouse's Planetarium V 1.01 User Guide


          Program and documentation written by J.Croudy 1991-1995


          @{"Introduction" LINK "Intro"}
          @{"Disclaimer" LINK "Disclaimer"}
          @{"Installation" LINK "Install"}
          @{"Configuration" LINK "Config"}
          @{"Main Screen" LINK "MainScr"}
          @{"Limitations" LINK "Limit"}
          @{"Acknowledgements" LINK "Thanks"}
          @{"Author's Personal Notes" LINK "Notes"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Intro" "Introduction"
@PREV "MAIN"
@TOC "MAIN"

          Introduction.

          Pink  Mouse's  Planetarium  is your own personal Planetarium and
          Time  Machine.   It  can display a graphic representation of the
          sky, as seen from almost anywhere on Earth, for any time between
          9999  BC and 9999 AD, and give information on any object you can
          see on the screen.  It can also display the Solar System as seen
          from space.

          The program was designed to allow the user to explore the beauty
          of  the  universe we live in from the comfort of their own home.
          It  should  appeal  to  anyone  who is interested in finding out
          about the sky.  The program will most probably be of most use in
          education, as it has a very limited object database.

@ENDNODE

